  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted informally and its findings are summarised in the UQ narrative, confirming that inlet flow rate and impeller rotational speed are the dominant contributors to hemolysis index variance. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and required levels met. Decision: Accepted.",
